node.text: Have to hand it to @valerialipovetsky for always finding ways to entertain the Lipovetsky brothers.

It's a lot less complicated than you think. Talent and Work, that's it. Both of these factors are under your control. Actually, one fuels the other. In order to develop talent, you need work. The more you work, the more talented you become. Other than that, reverse engineer the whole thing and ask yourself why you want to do this in the first place, hobby or business? If it's a hobby, cool, take it slow and enjoy. If it's to create a new business or accelerate an existing business, don't bother unless you're willing to put in the work. Valeria's built her audience to over 1.3M on YouTube and 500K on Instagram. I see first hand how much work it is. Not only is it not easy, but even if you hire a team to help you, it's still an overwhelming amount of work. Good luck!
Time goes by regardless, it’s what you choose to do with the time you’ve been given that determines your happiness.

It’s the start of a Lipovetsky men tradition. Benny and I are off on our boys trip, just me and him. About a year ago, I took Jake on this exact same trip and it was priceless. Taking each of my boys one on one for a few days on a trip is such a great way to bond. We get to be together without distractions and competing for attention. When you have a big family, it’s not only important to spend time all together, but also individually. After my trip with Jake, we feel so much closer and it was amazing that Jake wasn’t upset when he heard that Benny and I were going away. He said, “ohhhh, have fun guys, tell the alligators I said hi”. This trip is extra special because tomorrow is Benny’s 5th birthday 🎂.

Scale to Succeed. Had a call with an influencer today who’s at the point where they have a sustainable business. Great, fantastic, but what’s next I’m asked? “How do I get bigger”? Up until now, they’ve risked their time, not their money. Cool, but now you have to re-invest. So, figure out where most of your time is going and make your first hire. The person you hire will free your time to do whatever it is that moves your business forward (in this case making way more content). Yes, it will cost you money, but that’s how this works. Repeat over time, that’s how you grow your business. Because if you’re not growing, you’ll eventually start shrinking.
